'''恋鞋'''是一種[[性偏好|性偏好]]，有恋鞋情結的人常常會被對方的鞋子所吸引。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.who.int/classifications/apps/icd/icd10online/ |title=World Health Organization, International Statistical Classification of Diseases and Related Health Problems, (2007), Chapter V, F65.0 Disorders of sexual preference. |access-date=2022-05-29 |archive-date=2009-04-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090422160923/https://www.who.int/classifications/apps/icd/icd10online/ }}</ref><ref>[[Peter_Jerome_Fagan|Peter Jerome Fagan]]. Contributor [[Paul_R_McHugh|Paul R McHugh]]. Sexual Disorders: Perspectives on Diagnosis and Treatment. JHU Press. 2003. {{ISBN|0-8018-7527-7}}. p.78</ref>據調查，在對与人體相关的物体有性偏好的人群中有64%的人喜歡鞋子、靴子和其他鞋类。<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Scorolli | first1 = C. | last2 = Ghirlanda | first2 = S. | last3 = Enquist | first3 = M. | last4 = Zattoni | first4 = S.|author5-link=Emmanuele A. Jannini | last5 = Jannini | first5 = E. A. | title = Relative prevalence of different fetishes | doi = 10.1038/sj.ijir.3901547 | journal = International Journal of Impotence Research | volume = 19 | issue = 4 | pages = 432–437 | year = 2007 | pmid = 17304204| doi-access = free }}</ref><ref>Dobson, Roger (2007). '' Heels are the world's No 1 fetish.'' The Independent Online Edition, {{cite web |url=http://news.independent.co.uk/world/science_technology/article2303022.ece |title=Archived copy |access-date=2007-02-01 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080520112041/http://news.independent.co.uk/world/science_technology/article2303022.ece |archive-date=2008-05-20 }}, accessed February 2007.</ref>

